A pedestrian was killed after being run over by a car on the N2 in the vicinity of Queen Nandi Drive, north of Durban, on Tuesday morning. Kyle van Reenen, Emer-G-Med spokesperson, said reports from the scene are that a man, approximately thirty years old, was struck by a car and died. He was declared dead on arrival of paramedics. “The driver of the vehicle, a woman approximately thirty five years old, suffered minor injuries and was treated and stabilised on scene before being taken to a nearby hospital for further care,” said Van Reenen.